```yaml
leads:
  - headline: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) in Autocomplete Results
    analysis: |
      The `AutocompleteController` uses the `item.text` property directly when rendering results in the `#createAutocompleteWithRemoteData` function. If the autocomplete endpoint returns user-generated content within the `text` field of the results, it could lead to an XSS vulnerability. An attacker could potentially inject malicious JavaScript code that would be executed in the context of other users' browsers when they view the autocomplete suggestions.
    cwe: CWE-79
    function_names:
      - #createAutocompleteWithRemoteData
    filenames:
      - assets/src/controller.ts
    classification: very promising
```
